Roxi eys sale of the Galaz Contract Area | Interactive Investor
Roxi Petroleum has entered into a non-binding heads of terms with Xinjiang Zhundong Petroleum Technology Co in relation to a sale of 100% of the Galaz Contract Area, Kazakhstan, for $100m, including the assumption of debt.
It was working with Xinjiang Zhundong and the other shareholders in Galaz. Roxi holds a 34.22% stake in Galaz. Xinjiang Zhundong has been granted exclusivity until Jan. 31.
At 9:17am: (LON:RXP) Roxi Petroleum PLC share price was +1.5p at 11p
